column5: Very sorry for your loss. Use your beautiful creation to comfort you through your emotional recovery. Take care.

Why did you choose him? I’m not being mean, I have been in this situation and you should really evaluate what made you choose your partner. His actions sound cruel and lacking in empathy. I caution you, if there were very tiny indications of this behavior before you married, chances are this will remain a problem. He sounds controlling and unfortunately women by nature are “ fixers.” It’s a tough combination of characters. Please take care and always hang on to who you are and your sense of self worth. You are a strong person.

Keep them growing, looking good. My aunt has serious seasonal depression, her indoor garden is her salvation. I work in the mental health field, you’re so right about therapeutic value. Plants don’t give you attitude. It’s great to read all these comments, keep it up.
The eyes tell the whole story.
Good luck! The decision to start is the biggest hurdle and you have already done that. I’m a life member, set small goals as you do this.
